[[File:Omaha-Village-Hall-il.jpg|thumb|Omaha Village Hall]]
As of the [[2020 United States census|2020 census]]<ref name=":0" /> there were 209 people, 91 households. The population density was {{Convert|280.54|PD/sqmi|PD/km2}}. There were 116 housing units at an average density of {{Convert|155.70|/sqmi|/km2}}. The racial makeup of the village was 95.22% [[White (U.S. Census)|White]], 0.48% [[Asian (U.S. Census)|Asian]], and 4.31% from two or more races.

The median income for a household in the village was $54,107, and the median income for a family was $71,250.  About 14.9% of the population were below the [[poverty line]], including 17.6% of those under age 18 and 12.3% of those age 65 or over.

